Mother Goddess Episode Four 02 December 2025

WEBVTT

00:00:28.635 --> 00:00:30.577
Welcome back to the Yada Yahowah Blog.

00:00:30.836 --> 00:00:32.259
I am your host, Yada.

00:00:32.999 --> 00:00:34.960
I say “welcome back” because this is the

00:00:35.100 --> 00:00:38.264
longest hiatus I think we have taken since

00:00:38.304 --> 00:00:42.228
we began doing this back in December of

00:00:42.408 --> 00:00:45.191
last year—almost a year ago now.

00:00:46.371 --> 00:00:49.034
For those who may not know,

00:00:50.148 --> 00:00:52.408
I suffered a little injury to my back.

00:00:52.488 --> 00:00:53.789
You probably,

00:00:54.250 --> 00:00:55.890
if you are a regular listener,

00:00:55.930 --> 00:00:58.993
know that we have three adorable dogs here.

00:00:59.033 --> 00:00:59.232
One fell sick.

00:01:01.334 --> 00:01:03.655
It was the biggest one of the three,

00:01:03.695 --> 00:01:05.316
who now weighs about eighty pounds.

00:01:06.016 --> 00:01:09.680
Because of the fever she had,

00:01:09.740 --> 00:01:12.424
she did not want to sleep alone.

00:01:12.805 --> 00:01:14.667
So I lifted her up and down off

00:01:14.807 --> 00:01:17.629
the bed at night and again in the morning

00:01:17.691 --> 00:01:21.094
for three days.

00:01:21.796 --> 00:01:23.216
In doing that,

00:01:25.376 --> 00:01:27.900
I put a lot of undue strain on the lower

00:01:27.939 --> 00:01:31.245
discs of my back. Then Wookie,

00:01:31.265 --> 00:01:33.808
the medium-sized one, almost had an accident

00:01:33.868 --> 00:01:37.033
and I twisted with the disc already compressed.

00:01:39.537 --> 00:01:42.319
Between what happened late Friday evening,

00:01:42.599 --> 00:01:44.921
Saturday, and Sunday,

00:01:45.662 --> 00:01:50.265
by Sunday I was quite a mess.

00:01:50.605 --> 00:01:53.766
It has been quite painful to recover,

00:01:53.807 --> 00:01:57.108
but I think almost everyone listening to this

00:01:57.168 --> 00:01:58.810
has gone through a period of back pain.

00:01:58.870 --> 00:02:00.631
I have had mine in the past,

00:02:00.691 --> 00:02:01.792
but not nearly as severe as many of you.

00:02:04.793 --> 00:02:06.534
I appreciate all of you who have shared

00:02:06.573 --> 00:02:06.875
your stories with me.

00:02:09.675 --> 00:02:12.396
It is very common for us to deal with these things.

00:02:14.197 --> 00:02:17.457
We are finding that over time, with lots

00:02:17.578 --> 00:02:22.819
of rest, icing, and caution,

00:02:24.140 --> 00:02:26.320
it is beginning to dissipate.

00:02:27.201 --> 00:02:28.562
Yesterday,

00:02:28.762 --> 00:02:30.082
as also on Sunday,

00:02:30.103 --> 00:02:32.282
I was able to spend considerable time

00:02:32.362 --> 00:02:34.383
still translating, studying, and writing,

00:02:35.104 --> 00:02:36.224
finding some things that are really fascinating

00:02:37.564 --> 00:02:40.486
back in the Garden, because that is truly therapeutic for me.

00:02:42.508 --> 00:02:43.268
The idea, though,

00:02:43.407 --> 00:02:45.229
of turning on these lights and the camera

00:02:45.348 --> 00:02:47.590
and sitting in this chair with one wrong move

00:02:47.650 --> 00:02:50.350
being like a knife in my back

00:02:50.390 --> 00:02:51.872
just did not seem like the right temperament

00:02:51.951 --> 00:02:55.274
to display for this program.

00:02:56.234 --> 00:02:59.756
So that is why we have had this hiatus.

00:03:01.356 --> 00:03:04.737
But I am delighted to be back with you.

00:03:04.777 --> 00:03:05.358
Since this was

00:03:07.500 --> 00:03:10.262
a Family Hour blog and it was Friday night

00:03:10.421 --> 00:03:14.506
when we last reviewed this material,

00:03:14.626 --> 00:03:16.167
I want to turn the page back a little

00:03:16.206 --> 00:03:18.949
to some of the opening statements Yahowah made

00:03:18.990 --> 00:03:20.931
regarding the Garden.

00:03:21.891 --> 00:03:24.554
We are going to go through it once again.

00:03:25.474 --> 00:03:26.096
And

00:03:26.756 --> 00:03:29.237
while this series is still under the title

00:03:29.298 --> 00:03:30.179
“Mother Goddesses,”

00:03:30.218 --> 00:03:32.599
that is really the furthest thing from my mind at this point.

00:03:34.801 --> 00:03:36.742
They have been thoroughly repudiated.

00:03:36.782 --> 00:03:38.764
If they choose to surface again and continue to

00:03:38.805 --> 00:03:42.086
demean me and Yada Yahowah, that is on them.

00:03:43.427 --> 00:03:45.590
I am pursuing this because

00:03:46.818 --> 00:03:51.280
of how profound the testimony is and how important and relevant it is.

00:03:53.760 --> 00:03:56.020
Some of the most interesting, insightful,

00:03:57.222 --> 00:04:01.543
and relevant pronouncements I have ever seen from God.

00:04:03.484 --> 00:04:07.765
It got to the point where this morning I was retranslating

00:04:07.825 --> 00:04:13.548
the statements placed in the serpent’s fangs, if you will,

00:04:14.782 --> 00:04:19.305
regarding what he said to Chawah.

00:04:23.408 --> 00:04:25.511
And I came to realize that it is Yahowah

00:04:26.571 --> 00:04:31.595
who wrote the script.

00:04:32.815 --> 00:04:33.576
What is actually said,

00:04:35.033 --> 00:04:38.415
when you get down to the nuances of Hebrew grammar

00:04:38.495 --> 00:04:41.858
and how it was conveyed using those nuances,

00:04:41.918 --> 00:04:45.761
is brilliant.

00:04:47.362 --> 00:04:49.903
It is just absolutely brilliant.

00:04:50.242 --> 00:04:54.125
I have spent years of my life exposing and condemning Satan’s rants

00:04:55.759 --> 00:04:58.221
in the Christian New Testament and in the Quran,

00:04:58.262 --> 00:05:00.543
as well as what he revealed about himself

00:05:00.584 --> 00:05:01.105
in the book of Yachezq’el | Ezekiel.

00:05:06.829 --> 00:05:09.312
So I think I know the Adversary pretty well.

00:05:11.053 --> 00:05:12.894
I am not impressed.

00:05:13.435 --> 00:05:15.036
He is just not that smart.

00:05:16.098 --> 00:05:18.279
And yet what I read in the dialogue

00:05:19.303 --> 00:05:22.706
between the serpent and Chawah,

00:05:22.805 --> 00:05:26.466
at least on the serpent’s part,

00:05:26.487 --> 00:05:30.769
is flat-out brilliant and prophetic.

00:05:31.428 --> 00:05:32.889
So I want to get back to that,

00:05:32.930 --> 00:05:35.690
but with the proper foundation,

00:05:35.711 --> 00:05:39.252
recognizing that what God had to say is such

00:05:42.081 --> 00:05:43.223
that He knew we would figure it out.

00:05:45.324 --> 00:05:46.985
I can almost see the smirk on His face

00:05:47.026 --> 00:05:52.790
as He wrote it this way, saying even to Moshe,

00:05:53.310 --> 00:05:54.531
who He had write it down,

00:05:54.571 --> 00:05:55.591
“Moshe,

00:05:55.632 --> 00:06:01.156
I know you are going to say the discussion is between the serpent and this woman,

00:06:01.735 --> 00:06:04.737
and therefore it should be second-person feminine singular.

00:06:05.158 --> 00:06:09.000
But I do not want you to write it that way.

00:06:09.942 --> 00:06:11.041
I want you to write “you” as

00:06:11.925 --> 00:06:12.786
second-person masculine plural.

00:06:13.447 --> 00:06:17.250
I want you to write it that way because eventually there is going to be a guy

00:06:17.790 --> 00:06:21.673
and I might have to cheat with him.

00:06:21.733 --> 00:06:22.713
It may take him a while,

00:06:25.654 --> 00:06:27.235
but he is going to figure it out.

00:06:27.416 --> 00:06:28.817
And when he does,

00:06:28.898 --> 00:06:31.819
we are going to have a lesson the world needs to hear.”

00:06:33.060 --> 00:06:35.541
And so, as I say,

00:06:35.581 --> 00:06:36.583
I can see tongue-in-cheek

00:06:36.759 --> 00:06:38.341
where Yahowah was saying,

00:06:38.560 --> 00:06:50.242
“Yes, Moshe, that is the way I want it written down.

00:06:52.504 --> 00:06:54.065
I know you would say it is not grammatically correct,

00:06:57.168 --> 00:06:58.949
but listen,

00:07:01.771 --> 00:07:04.533
we are not recording this for Chawah—she is long gone.

00:07:07.492 --> 00:07:10.216
And the Children of Israel whom you are going to share this with

00:07:10.235 --> 00:07:11.997
are not going to understand it.

00:07:13.879 --> 00:07:16.122
It is for another time.”

00:07:16.283 --> 00:07:20.968
And sure enough, it took me a while,

00:07:21.009 --> 00:07:21.490
but I found it.

00:07:22.505 --> 00:07:23.966
I want to get back to that place

00:07:24.026 --> 00:07:24.807
and share it with you.

00:07:25.387 --> 00:07:26.788
So that is why we are going to turn the page back

00:07:26.827 --> 00:07:29.689
and begin really at the beginning of this narrative.

00:07:30.528 --> 00:07:31.649
It reads:

00:07:32.168 --> 00:07:34.509
Yahowah,

00:07:34.569 --> 00:07:37.411
which is a transliteration as instructed by Yahowah’s Torah teaching regarding His

00:07:37.471 --> 00:07:39.331
higher existence, Almighty,

00:07:40.192 --> 00:07:42.252
planted and established,

00:07:42.392 --> 00:07:47.334
firmly embedding a home to celebrate life

00:07:48.357 --> 00:07:50.197
as a Gan,

00:07:50.937 --> 00:07:53.238
which is a sheltered and protected,

00:07:53.678 --> 00:07:56.879
surrounded and enclosed garden.

00:07:59.141 --> 00:08:00.701
He called it 'Eden—

00:08:01.362 --> 00:08:03.483
great pleasure and joy.

00:08:04.122 --> 00:08:07.305
Pursuant to a time long ago,

00:08:07.925 --> 00:08:10.685
then He placed, He put,

00:08:10.766 --> 00:08:13.286
setting the man, Adam,

00:08:14.007 --> 00:08:15.548
He had fashioned and formed,

00:08:15.588 --> 00:08:16.447
He had designed,

00:08:16.487 --> 00:08:17.968
prepared and fabricated

00:08:19.524 --> 00:08:22.687
there for the benefit of the relationship

00:08:22.726 --> 00:08:25.588
and to show the way

00:08:25.608 --> 00:08:28.310
Bare’syth | in the beginning – Bare’syth / Genesis 2:8.

00:08:28.331 --> 00:08:30.312
So there are some things here that

00:08:30.333 --> 00:08:33.554
warrant our investigation.

00:08:33.575 --> 00:08:35.777
I am going to proceed in the only way I know how,

00:08:35.817 --> 00:08:41.000
which is that this message is vitally important,

00:08:41.480 --> 00:08:42.841
God is a brilliant communicator,

00:08:43.894 --> 00:08:47.537
and there are insights all along the way that He intended for us to know.

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:57.985
This message is literally life and death.

00:08:59.125 --> 00:09:01.008
So I am going to take the risk

00:09:02.207 --> 00:09:06.289
of overwhelming and turning away those of you who do not have the appetite

00:09:06.330 --> 00:09:08.551
for in-depth analysis,

00:09:09.892 --> 00:09:12.153
those who prefer sound bites,

00:09:12.393 --> 00:09:15.453
who think that a ten-word post on X is eight words too many.

00:09:18.654 --> 00:09:19.596
I am going to lose you.

00:09:20.475 --> 00:09:22.297
But I never had you anyway.

00:09:22.376 --> 00:09:22.596
In fact,

00:09:22.616 --> 00:09:24.057
there was never any hope for you anyway.

00:09:24.815 --> 00:09:27.336
I am going to assume that those who are listening

00:09:27.456 --> 00:09:30.937
are genuinely interested in knowing the profound truths regarding

00:09:30.977 --> 00:09:33.480
Yahowah so that they have the opportunity

00:09:33.519 --> 00:09:37.682
to earn His trust.

00:09:42.264 --> 00:09:43.384
Now this is a very,

00:09:43.424 --> 00:09:45.206
very different concept than anything

00:09:45.346 --> 00:09:46.687
anyone, including myself,

00:09:46.746 --> 00:09:49.368
has perceived up to this point.

00:09:50.580 --> 00:09:50.860
You see,

00:09:51.080 --> 00:09:52.980
what I have learned by going back to the story of Gan 'Eden,

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:56.023
to the Garden,

00:09:57.384 --> 00:10:00.166
is that Yahowah caused the fall of man

00:10:00.666 --> 00:10:01.767
because, quite frankly,

00:10:01.826 --> 00:10:04.028
He was both bored with man and He knew He could not trust man

00:10:04.048 --> 00:10:05.869
and that man had nothing to offer.

00:10:09.191 --> 00:10:12.953
So the reason man was exiled from the Garden

00:10:13.014 --> 00:10:16.115
and would have to fend for himself

00:10:18.700 --> 00:10:22.260
is because God wanted to give us time

00:10:22.301 --> 00:10:24.442
rather than foreclosing on the whole human experience

00:10:24.501 --> 00:10:26.682
and saying, “That did not work. What was I thinking?”

00:10:29.702 --> 00:10:31.703
He put us out of the Garden so

00:10:31.744 --> 00:10:35.205
that we would have the opportunity to resolve the deficiencies of Adam and Chawah.

00:10:40.667 --> 00:10:41.386
And they are:

00:10:42.567 --> 00:10:43.888
Adam was a deadbeat.

00:10:44.982 --> 00:10:47.043
He did not engage.

00:10:47.423 --> 00:10:51.346
He contributed nothing to the relationship or to the Garden.

00:10:53.606 --> 00:10:56.768
God is looking for co-workers,

00:10:56.967 --> 00:10:58.629
for co-workers plural,

00:10:59.328 --> 00:11:01.070
for those He can engage with,

00:11:01.129 --> 00:11:03.530
for those He can do things with,

00:11:03.551 --> 00:11:05.191
that He can build and achieve and accomplish something with.

00:11:07.272 --> 00:11:08.592
God is not lazy.

00:11:09.703 --> 00:11:10.323
He is a doer.

00:11:11.004 --> 00:11:11.823
He wants doers.

00:11:12.445 --> 00:11:13.325
Adam was not a doer.

00:11:14.085 --> 00:11:20.086
So if you understand where Adam failed and what God was looking for,

00:11:20.145 --> 00:11:21.886
you and I have the opportunity to become

00:11:22.927 --> 00:11:26.868
what God wants to see and experience in us.

00:11:32.950 --> 00:11:33.230
You see,

00:11:33.269 --> 00:11:35.910
the issue was that in that Garden,

00:11:35.951 --> 00:11:37.270
that sheltered enclosure,

00:11:37.931 --> 00:11:39.211
there were no challenges.

00:11:39.990 --> 00:11:42.351
Everything was provided.

00:11:42.912 --> 00:11:45.831
Adam did not have to work unless he chose to work.

00:11:46.812 --> 00:11:49.873
Adam did not have to listen unless he chose to listen.

00:11:50.732 --> 00:11:53.354
He did not have to respond to God unless he wanted to.

00:11:56.614 --> 00:11:59.254
He did not have to be trustworthy.

00:11:59.315 --> 00:12:00.715
But without those things,

00:12:02.500 --> 00:12:05.081
God was not interested in him.

00:12:05.140 --> 00:12:06.402
And you do not have to do any of those things either.

00:12:06.422 --> 00:12:07.182
But if you want God to trust you

00:12:07.643 --> 00:12:11.605
off of this planet into the universe that He conceived

00:12:12.745 --> 00:12:15.787
with two trillion galaxies,

00:12:15.826 --> 00:12:21.690
each with hundreds of billions of stars and countless planets and moons,

00:12:30.784 --> 00:12:34.106
such that He can go off and explore this universe

00:12:34.147 --> 00:12:37.648
and share it with you and trust you

00:12:37.727 --> 00:12:42.149
and expect you to listen and respond appropriately

00:12:42.211 --> 00:12:45.111
and for you to want to learn and to make the result better,

00:12:50.234 --> 00:12:52.916
then we have a lot that we need to process.

00:12:54.096 --> 00:12:57.618
We have the opportunity to prove ourselves.

00:12:59.001 --> 00:13:01.283
That is why He is reopening the Garden.

00:13:01.523 --> 00:13:03.864
That is why He has talked about the two trees

00:13:03.903 --> 00:13:05.083
that were in the Garden

00:13:05.104 --> 00:13:07.085
and particularly the 'Ets ha-Da'ath | Tree of Knowledge.

00:13:07.884 --> 00:13:08.826
Because without it,

00:13:08.946 --> 00:13:10.667
we do not get back to the Garden.

00:13:11.427 --> 00:13:11.927
Without it,

00:13:12.047 --> 00:13:14.128
we cannot benefit from the 'Ets Chayim | Tree of Lives.

00:13:15.269 --> 00:13:17.192
Without it we cannot grow.

00:13:17.231 --> 00:13:18.231
We cannot learn.

00:13:18.293 --> 00:13:20.875
We cannot become what God wants us to be.

00:13:21.615 --> 00:13:23.356
And that is the message we are conveying here.

00:13:24.177 --> 00:13:26.259
So when I say I could care less about the mother goddesses

00:13:26.359 --> 00:13:28.640
and that annoying cult, that is what I mean.

00:13:32.224 --> 00:13:34.586
The insights here are way too profound,

00:13:34.666 --> 00:13:41.350
way too important to God.

00:13:41.392 --> 00:13:43.753
For the first time I see it.

00:13:44.753 --> 00:13:48.677
I understand why the experience in the Garden failed,

00:13:48.716 --> 00:13:50.839
why God caused the fall of man.

00:13:55.224 --> 00:13:58.626
He wanted to show that it was possible for us to get back up.

00:14:01.169 --> 00:14:04.873
He knew that given the time and energy and effort required,

00:14:04.993 --> 00:14:05.673
there would be those of us who would stand again,

00:14:10.320 --> 00:14:11.860
who would rise to the occasion,

00:14:12.301 --> 00:14:16.163
who would be sufficiently interesting for God to trust off this planet.

00:14:18.764 --> 00:14:19.664
And as I say,

00:14:19.705 --> 00:14:21.626
the whole reason He is bringing us back to the Garden

00:14:21.667 --> 00:14:25.668
is that He is going to purge the least religious, least political,

00:14:25.749 --> 00:14:28.650
most open-minded people

00:14:28.951 --> 00:14:30.792
remnant of Israel that survives the next

00:14:35.102 --> 00:14:36.303
seven and a half years,

00:14:36.845 --> 00:14:40.287
such that when the time comes

00:14:41.788 --> 00:14:44.350
they will be the beneficiaries of the 'Ets ha-Da'ath

00:14:44.390 --> 00:14:47.474
and of those who are harvesting the Tree’s fruit.

00:14:50.956 --> 00:14:53.458
Then they can learn, they can grow,

00:14:54.438 --> 00:14:56.941
they can listen, they can respond,

00:14:57.907 --> 00:15:01.570
they can work and make a contribution.

00:15:02.169 --> 00:15:04.951
And those who do these things will have the opportunity

00:15:04.971 --> 00:15:08.474
of earning Yahowah’s trust and respect

00:15:08.533 --> 00:15:10.855
such that He is willing to go off-planet with us

00:15:10.895 --> 00:15:13.277
into additional dimensions in time.

00:15:20.581 --> 00:15:21.982
That is the message here.

00:15:22.543 --> 00:15:25.004
It is important that you have an appreciation of it.

00:15:28.727 --> 00:15:29.591
So it is Yahowah.

00:15:30.232 --> 00:15:32.258
If somebody gives you any other name,

00:15:33.020 --> 00:15:34.344
they are deceiving you.

00:15:35.764 --> 00:15:37.966
We know the pronunciation of Yahowah’s name.

00:15:39.427 --> 00:15:43.028
I am going through this in detail because

00:15:43.208 --> 00:15:46.510
it is the details that build the foundation of knowledge

00:15:46.591 --> 00:15:50.373
that enables you and me to make the necessary connections

00:15:50.552 --> 00:15:53.914
between things so that we come to comprehend

00:15:53.975 --> 00:15:56.476
the very nature of God,

00:15:59.979 --> 00:16:01.799
what He is offering and expecting in return.

00:16:04.724 --> 00:16:07.246
Then we can make an informed decision.

00:16:07.267 --> 00:16:08.187
We can act accordingly.

00:16:12.171 --> 00:16:14.693
Yahowah is God’s one and only name.

00:16:15.073 --> 00:16:17.777
If somebody tells you it is Yahweh, Yahovah,

00:16:19.658 --> 00:16:25.063
Jehovah, Hashem, Allah, or Jesus,

00:16:27.166 --> 00:16:27.726
they are lying to you.

00:16:29.701 --> 00:16:31.121
It is Yahowah,

00:16:31.182 --> 00:16:32.982
and we know it is Yahowah because when

00:16:33.023 --> 00:16:36.624
Yahowah revealed His name to Moshe from that burning fire

00:16:36.663 --> 00:16:39.546
on the crag atop Mount Horeb,

00:16:39.605 --> 00:16:43.827
He specifically said that His name was based on the verb Hayah,

00:16:44.408 --> 00:16:46.729
one of the most common verbs throughout the Torah.

00:16:46.808 --> 00:16:49.149
There is no question how Hayah is to be pronounced.

00:16:49.210 --> 00:16:52.072
He wrote it in first person, which would be 'ehayah.

00:16:57.846 --> 00:16:59.307
Yah is the first syllable of Yahowah’s name.

00:17:03.370 --> 00:17:06.951
Yah is the first syllable of Yahowah’s name.

00:17:08.012 --> 00:17:09.252
You can make it Yah,

00:17:10.193 --> 00:17:13.076
but the Y in Hebrew is pronounced identically to the Y in English.

00:17:15.676 --> 00:17:18.939
It is where we get the pronunciation.

00:17:19.798 --> 00:17:23.121
So it is Yah, as in Hayah.

00:17:23.862 --> 00:17:26.143
And the ending syllable is “ah,” as in “hi-ah.”

00:17:28.730 --> 00:17:32.172
The yod and hey are open-mouth vowel sounds in Hebrew.

00:17:34.772 --> 00:17:39.634
So it is Yah.

00:17:44.654 --> 00:17:46.515
And then the only question is, what about the “wah”?

00:17:46.674 --> 00:17:47.355
Because the “wah” is not in Hayah—hey, yod, hey.

00:17:47.375 --> 00:17:49.836
And this is yod, hey, wah, hey.

00:17:56.097 --> 00:17:57.778
Well, we do not have to look very far.

00:17:59.328 --> 00:17:59.949
When God says,

00:18:00.028 --> 00:18:02.931
“I want to provide teaching and guidance,

00:18:04.030 --> 00:18:05.912
direction and instruction,

00:18:06.732 --> 00:18:08.153
and I am going to provide it in a book,

00:18:08.314 --> 00:18:10.835
and I am going to have Moshe scribe that book for you,”

00:18:10.914 --> 00:18:15.958
what does He call that book?

00:18:15.978 --> 00:18:16.597
The Towrah.

00:18:17.778 --> 00:18:19.619
Ah, Towrah, right.

00:18:20.039 --> 00:18:22.840
Towrah has that “ah” ending too, does it not?

00:18:22.861 --> 00:18:26.682
So that certainly affirms the two “ah”s in Yahowah’s name.

00:18:29.036 --> 00:18:30.057
But what about that other letter?

00:18:30.557 --> 00:18:33.919
The “wah” makes the “o” sound.

00:18:33.939 --> 00:18:39.461
That is how you get the sound Towrah.

00:18:40.201 --> 00:18:41.001
Unfortunately,

00:18:41.603 --> 00:18:45.305
rabbis have removed the “wah” from their depiction of Towrah

00:18:45.325 --> 00:18:48.606
just to mislead so that you would not know it.

00:18:49.926 --> 00:18:52.008
The most common greeting in Hebrew is shalowm.

00:18:53.828 --> 00:18:55.710
The “o” sound in shalowm comes from the Hebrew “wah.”

00:18:56.971 --> 00:18:58.592
But Towrah is sufficient.

00:19:01.396 --> 00:19:05.161
So with the “o” sound from Towrah derived from the “wah,”

00:19:05.201 --> 00:19:05.761
we know how to pronounce Yahowah’s name.

00:19:07.364 --> 00:19:08.384
It is that simple.

00:19:08.525 --> 00:19:09.727
It is that obvious.

00:19:10.207 --> 00:19:13.431
And yet for two thousand five hundred years no one pronounced it.

00:19:17.234 --> 00:19:18.737
No one knew its pronunciation.

00:19:20.118 --> 00:19:22.040
But I did, and I did it in

00:19:23.536 --> 00:19:25.636
Volume One of An Introduction to God

00:19:25.817 --> 00:19:29.699
called “To Know Yahowah” where I looked at

00:19:30.058 --> 00:19:34.701
every word in the Hebrew lexicon that contained a yod, hey, and wah

00:19:39.604 --> 00:19:43.786
and examined how those vowels were pronounced

00:19:44.527 --> 00:19:48.288
because you cannot claim that there are eight or ten thousand words

00:19:49.128 --> 00:19:52.151
in the Towrah, Prophets, and Psalms

00:19:52.191 --> 00:19:52.611
of which seven thousand nine hundred ninety-nine are pronounceable

00:19:53.692 --> 00:19:55.453
but one is not.

00:20:04.463 --> 00:20:07.528
That is just stupid when every word is comprised of the same twenty-two letters,

00:20:07.587 --> 00:20:09.430
seventeen consonants, five vowels.

00:20:15.560 --> 00:20:17.561
So I looked at every single word and every name

00:20:17.663 --> 00:20:20.364
and everything you could say, “Well, that is overwhelming proof there, is it not?”

00:20:24.507 --> 00:20:26.067
Like shalowm and Towrah.

00:20:27.489 --> 00:20:29.349
And I wrote an entire chapter on the pronunciation of Yahowah’s name.

00:20:31.192 --> 00:20:33.873
So I am the first in two thousand five hundred years to introduce it

00:20:33.893 --> 00:20:35.454
and to prove that that is the proper pronunciation of it.

00:20:40.670 --> 00:20:44.011
