It is a way to perceive Bikuwrym,

00:56:26.802 --> 00:56:27.702
firstborn children.

00:56:28.284 --> 00:56:30.043
That is the result of Pesach, Matsah, and Bikuwrym

00:56:30.083 --> 00:56:31.824
being fulfilled by Dowd.

00:56:32.704 --> 00:56:36.226
And on Pesach as the Passover Lamb,

00:56:37.759 --> 00:56:39.880
He was crucified, His body,

00:56:40.460 --> 00:56:43.561
to open that doorway to life on Pesach,

00:56:44.240 --> 00:56:45.320
such that on Matsah,

00:56:45.681 --> 00:56:49.322
His nefesh soul carried our guilt into She’owl, a black hole,

00:56:51.802 --> 00:56:53.302
never to be seen again,

00:56:55.704 --> 00:56:57.684
making us appear perfect in God’s eyes,

00:56:58.744 --> 00:57:01.405
expunging all of that nastiness from us

00:57:01.865 --> 00:57:03.465
so we can be exposed to God and feel great about it.

00:57:04.887 --> 00:57:05.827
He sees the best in us.

00:57:07.478 --> 00:57:11.579
And this leads to where God says specifically,

00:57:11.659 --> 00:57:14.760
we are enriched by Him, empowered by Him,

00:57:15.201 --> 00:57:16.121
both to a magnitude of tenfold

00:57:16.802 --> 00:57:24.664
and adopted into His Family.

00:57:27.646 --> 00:57:32.708
That is what we see behind that doorway to life, which is 'Eden.

00:57:41.135 --> 00:57:48.219
It is a pretty remarkable word, is it not?

00:57:48.239 --> 00:57:50.000
Well, that is one statement.

00:57:50.039 --> 00:57:51.920
We are an hour into our program,

00:57:52.900 --> 00:57:54.141
and we have covered one statement.

00:57:55.161 --> 00:57:57.284
And this is even in review of where we were previously

00:57:57.344 --> 00:58:00.304
in our previous program.

00:58:01.826 --> 00:58:07.309
So if you want to be frustrated about my diligence,

00:58:08.219 --> 00:58:09.260
you probably are not going to pass muster

00:58:09.400 --> 00:58:12.143
with what God is looking for.

00:58:14.184 --> 00:58:14.983
Because I want to tell you,

00:58:15.003 --> 00:58:17.505
the level of diligence we just applied to this

00:58:17.545 --> 00:58:20.088
is nothing compared to where we are going.

00:58:22.128 --> 00:58:24.311
So, you know,

00:58:24.331 --> 00:58:26.431
pour yourself a cup of tea, a cup of coffee,

00:58:26.572 --> 00:58:28.092
whatever it is that floats your boat.

00:58:28.994 --> 00:58:30.514
Settle in and join us.

00:58:31.454 --> 00:58:33.376
Be comfortable.

00:58:35.239 --> 00:58:36.760
We have a lot to learn.

00:58:37.041 --> 00:58:38.442
We have got a lot to achieve.

00:58:38.862 --> 00:58:40.985
We have only got eight years to filter through

00:58:41.005 --> 00:58:43.668
those who are going to be the helpers,

00:58:46.909 --> 00:58:48.690
dishing out, if you will,

00:58:48.989 --> 00:58:50.471
the fruit of the Tree of Knowledge,

00:58:51.891 --> 00:58:54.855
and then to purge this final remnant of Gowym and Yehudym

00:58:54.934 --> 00:58:59.358
such that we are enabling them to celebrate Dowd’s return with Yahowah

00:58:59.617 --> 00:59:04.800
on Kippurym and then enter the restored Garden on Sukkah

00:59:04.840 --> 00:59:07.463
such that we can equip them over the next thousand years

00:59:07.503 --> 00:59:10.144
to be trusted to go explore off this planet.

00:59:15.110 --> 00:59:16.472
We do not have a lot of time.

00:59:19.012 --> 00:59:20.132
We have got a lot to accomplish.

00:59:22.594 --> 00:59:24.715
So it is important that we focus on what God is saying.

00:59:26.876 --> 00:59:29.418
I guess now if we do one verse per show,

00:59:29.458 --> 00:59:29.918
we should finish this within that thousand-year window, do you not think?

00:59:34.179 --> 00:59:34.500
Yeah,

00:59:34.519 --> 00:59:35.960
I think within the thousand-year window.

00:59:37.061 --> 00:59:38.442
Not within the eight years we have remaining.

00:59:40.222 --> 00:59:41.163
But you know, we have time.

00:59:43.186 --> 00:59:45.266
So, yeah, well, who is God Almighty?

00:59:46.206 --> 00:59:49.827
He enabled life to sprout up and grow.

00:59:51.168 --> 00:59:51.708
Shamak.

00:59:53.309 --> 00:59:59.851
Shamak is and shamak are related words.

00:01:00:01.153 --> 00:01:00:04.436
The Shemek of Yahowah is Dowd.

00:01:00:04.516 --> 00:01:00:07.117
That is the great branch of the Tree of Lives.

00:01:00:08.518 --> 00:01:01:11.239
And Shemek, the verbal root of it,

00:01:01:11.820 --> 00:01:01:14.081
means to sprout and grow.

00:01:01:15.222 --> 00:01:01:17.163
Dowd is the doorway to life.

00:01:01:17.182 --> 00:01:01:20.945
It was that upright pole that was once a tree

00:01:01:20.965 --> 00:01:01:23.465
that he was affixed to on Passover

00:01:01:23.525 --> 00:01:01:27.367
that opened that doorway to life.

00:01:01:30.014 --> 00:01:01:31.554
Yes, he was crucified,

00:01:01:31.594 --> 00:01:01:35.815
fulfilling Passover on a tree because he is the 'Ets Chayym,

00:01:01:35.914 --> 00:01:01:41.757
the Tree of Lives.

00:01:01:43.237 --> 00:01:01:45.378
And as the main branch,

00:01:01:46.858 --> 00:01:50.199
God says that his purpose is for us to grow.

00:01:01:50.239 --> 00:01:01:51.239
He enabled our growth.

00:01:01:55.800 --> 00:01:01:56.621
To grow is to live,

00:01:01:56.960 --> 00:01:01:57.661
to live is to grow.

00:01:01:58.938 --> 00:01:01:04.302
You stop growing, you stop living.

00:01:01:04.322 --> 00:01:01:06.684
He initiated and caused life to increase

00:01:01:06.744 --> 00:01:01:09.505
in a variety of ways and in stature while promoting growth.

00:01:01:11.266 --> 00:01:01:15.690
Hiphil means that it was Yahowah who did these things through the object.

00:01:01:15.730 --> 00:01:01:20.393
So Yahowah is the subject.

00:01:01:20.414 --> 00:01:01:23.014
The object here would be ha-'adamah.

00:01:01:27.557 --> 00:01:01:27.739
So

00:01:01:28.550 --> 00:01:01:30.731
you can say that ha-'adamah is the ground of the earth,

00:01:01:30.771 --> 00:01:01:31.391
or you can recognize that 'adamah is a title

00:01:01:35.434 --> 00:01:01:38.054
that Yahowah uses and it is ha-'adamah here,

00:01:01:38.094 --> 00:01:01:38.394
and he is the bloody red man of the earth.

00:01:01:42.617 --> 00:01:01:45.518
And so Yahowah is saying that He enabled life to grow

00:01:01:45.858 --> 00:01:01:52.182
from what is represented by ha-'adamah,

00:01:01:52.242 --> 00:01:01:52.722
this bloody red man of the earth.

00:01:01:53.202 --> 00:01:01:54.523
Or you can just look at it simplistically and say, ah,

00:01:01:57.731 --> 00:01:01:59.911
do not bother me with that prophecy stuff.

00:01:02:00.010 --> 00:01:02:02.552
I do not want to know these connections between things.

00:01:02:02.592 --> 00:01:02:03.492
Just dumb it down to my level.

00:01:02:06.112 --> 00:01:02:09.773
He was allowed to grow from the soil, from the dirt.

00:01:02:14.034 --> 00:01:02:14.954
But if that is all it is,

00:01:02:16.994 --> 00:01:02:20.396
then why is 'Adamah just the version of 'Adam?

00:01:02:23.498 --> 00:01:02:27.862
Why does 'Adam mean red, bloody red color?

00:01:02:31.465 --> 00:01:02:32.945
Why would He not use just 'eretz?

00:01:02:32.985 --> 00:01:02:33.646
It means ground.

00:01:02:35.327 --> 00:01:02:36.088
Why ha-'adamah?

00:01:02:36.309 --> 00:01:41.112
Why the definite article?

00:01:02:44.213 --> 00:01:02:47.416
What does ha-'adamah contribute?

00:01:02:48.427 --> 00:01:02:51.911
Because ha-'adamah is darn near as important to this story of the Garden

00:01:02:52.291 --> 00:01:02:55.434
as is the 'Ets ha-Da'ath, the Tree of Knowledge.

00:01:03:02.001 --> 00:01:02:02.882
Happened to be the same fellow.

00:01:03:04.641 --> 00:01:03:06.302
God is telling you a story that you can brush through

00:01:03:06.342 --> 00:01:03:09.465
and say, yeah, so you would not know Yahowah’s name

00:01:03:13.266 --> 00:01:03:14.568
if you are brushing through

00:01:03:14.588 --> 00:01:03:16.228
because none of the translations present it.

00:01:03:16.889 --> 00:01:03:22.893
And they do not recognize that it says God following it.

00:01:03:23.273 --> 00:01:03:23.853
So it would be,

00:01:03:23.914 --> 00:01:03:24.693
they are going to tell you the Lord God.

00:01:03:28.476 --> 00:01:03:33.420
And then cause life,

00:01:03:35.173 --> 00:01:03:37.115
made life, initiated life.

00:01:03:38.637 --> 00:01:03:43.023
And they do not tell you that shamach is Dowd.

00:01:03:44.603 --> 00:01:03:47.146
So here you have what I call the two fellows.

00:01:03:47.166 --> 00:01:03:47.688
In Bare’syth one,

00:01:03:49.108 --> 00:01:03:55.016
you have the Gadowl and the katan,

00:01:03:56.652 --> 00:01:03:59.733
the greater and lesser luminaries.

00:01:03:59.773 --> 00:01:04:02.295
They are the signs for the Mowedym,

00:01:04:02.835 --> 00:01:04:03.376
the restoring witnesses to the eternal testimony.

00:01:04:05.556 --> 00:01:04:07.277
And then in Bare’syth two, Genesis two,

00:01:04:17.342 --> 00:01:04:22.085
you have the 'Ets of Chayym and the 'Ets of Da'ath.

00:01:04:26.061 --> 00:01:04:28.862
Same two guys.

00:01:04:28.882 --> 00:01:04:32.143
And here you have the Shamach and the 'Adamah.

00:01:04:34.784 --> 00:01:04:35.505
Same two fellows.

00:01:04:36.365 --> 00:01:04:38.487
Dowd is the greater luminary.

00:01:04:38.646 --> 00:01:01:41.248
Yada is the lesser luminary reflecting the greater luminary’s light.

00:01:04:41.288 --> 00:01:04:42.389
They both serve as signs for the Mowedym,

00:01:04:42.728 --> 00:01:04:44.409
which they happen to be the two fellows that actually fulfill Mowedym.

00:01:04:45.389 --> 00:01:04:47.030
The Tree of Knowledge leads to the Tree of Lives.

00:01:04:53.025 --> 00:01:04:53.565
And the fellow that is the Tree of Knowledge

00:01:04:53.686 --> 00:01:04:55.146
happens to be the first person to recognize

00:01:04:55.186 --> 00:01:04:57.168
that Dowd is the Tree of Lives.

00:01:04:59.849 --> 00:01:05:01.110
And oh, by the way, the Choter,

00:01:05:01.371 --> 00:01:05:02.192
which is Yada,

00:01:05:02.952 --> 00:01:05:07.596
is specifically presented as the 'Ets of Da'ath.

00:01:05:09.237 --> 00:01:05:13.079
So he is the Tree of Knowledge.

00:01:05:13.099 --> 00:01:05:13.840
Same two fellows.

00:01:05:14.661 --> 00:01:05:15.762
And here they are again.

00:01:05:17.934 --> 00:01:05:19.675
Shamach and 'Adamah.

00:01:05:19.695 --> 00:01:05:23.617
Oh, okay, Dowd gets the good part.

00:01:05:24.278 --> 00:01:05:27.780
He is the big honking branch that sprouts and grows, that enables life.

00:01:05:29.641 --> 00:01:05:31.362
And you know, I am the soil,

00:01:05:32.485 --> 00:01:05:34.025
bloody red man of the earth from which it grows.

00:01:05:34.065 --> 00:01:05:34.545
I am happy, by the way.

00:01:05:34.565 --> 00:01:05:36.186
I am just kidding here.

00:01:05:36.206 --> 00:01:05:37.626
I mean, yes,

00:01:05:37.646 --> 00:01:05:38.407
I know that I am the lesser luminary.

00:01:05:38.507 --> 00:01:05:41.047
He is the greater luminary.

00:01:05:41.108 --> 00:01:05:42.387
I am the bloody red man of the earth,

00:01:05:46.128 --> 00:01:05:48.728
and he is this massive branch that promotes growth,

00:01:05:48.789 --> 00:01:05:49.949
and he is the Tree of Lives,

00:01:05:52.750 --> 00:01:05:56.130
and I am the knowledge that points back to him.

00:01:05:58.030 --> 00:01:05:58.710
Dowd is the guy.

00:01:06:00.947 --> 00:01:06:02.831
And you better have fun with the realization that he is the guy

00:01:06:03.092 --> 00:01:06:05.715
and the best you can hope for is having the opportunity to serve him

00:01:06:05.735 --> 00:01:06:08.541
because he works with Yahowah

00:01:06:12.768 --> 00:01:06:13.349
and he is

00:01:06:13.735 --> 00:01:06:15.896
Dowd then wants to work with others who are similarly devoted and committed to learning,

00:01:06:16.016 --> 00:01:06:19.338
who are, well, as Yahowah was looking for,

00:01:06:19.478 --> 00:01:06:21.039
someone willing to work, to engage, to make a contribution,

00:01:06:25.503 --> 00:01:06:27.384
somebody willing to listen and respond appropriately,

00:01:06:27.423 --> 00:01:06:28.085
and somebody who shows fortitude

00:01:06:28.545 --> 00:01:06:31.666
and is willing to get up when they have fallen so that they are reliable.

00:01:06:35.210 --> 00:01:06:36.891
Dowd is looking for exactly the same qualifications that Yahowah is,

00:01:06:39.692 --> 00:01:06:41.753
and Yahowah chose Dowd because, well,

00:01:06:41.833 --> 00:01:06:43.813
he was a fellow who managed to get up every time he fell,

00:01:06:43.855 --> 00:01:06:44.914
who was always willing to listen to Yahowah,

00:01:06:47.195 --> 00:01:06:47.556
who was constantly learning and growing,

00:01:06:50.518 --> 00:01:06:52.798
and whom God could trust and rely upon,

00:01:06:52.858 --> 00:01:06:54.440
particularly in the fulfillment of Pesach, Matsah, and Bikuwrym.

00:01:06:57.121 --> 00:01:06:58.581
And he was a worker.

00:01:06:59.681 --> 00:01:07:00.362
He was a goer.

00:01:07:00.382 --> 00:01:07:01.043
He was a doer.

00:01:07:02.847 --> 00:01:07:06.010
So these are the things.

00:01:07:06.030 --> 00:01:07:08.472
This is how they work together in God’s story.

00:01:07:09.391 --> 00:01:07:11.134
I mean, every time you look around.

00:01:07:12.954 --> 00:01:07:13.916
It is the same thing.

00:01:07:16.177 --> 00:01:07:18.539
Yeah.

00:01:07:18.579 --> 00:01:07:22.322
God has got two guys.

00:01:07:22.342 --> 00:01:07:23.885
There is the lesser and greater luminary,

00:01:07:24.884 --> 00:01:07:25.344
there is the Tree of Knowledge that leads to the Tree of Lives.

00:01:07:27.967 --> 00:01:07:31.469
There is the ha-'adamah that is the source

00:01:07:31.489 --> 00:01:07:34.813
from which the shamach sprouts up and grows.

00:01:07:35.432 --> 00:01:07:36.693
Without the ha-'adamah,

00:01:07:36.713 --> 00:01:07:37.875
this bloody red man of the earth,

00:01:07:39.197 --> 00:01:07:42.239
then nobody knows about the Tree of Lives.

00:01:07:42.980 --> 00:01:07:43.740
They do not know who it is,

00:01:07:43.760 --> 00:01:07:46.302
do not know how to return to it.

00:01:07:46.342 --> 00:01:07:47.923
So they support each other in this role.

00:01:07:48.043 --> 00:01:07:51.987
This is God’s plan from the beginning.

00:01:07:54.528 --> 00:01:07:56.110
It is marvelous.

00:01:07:57.210 --> 00:01:07:59.851
This is the cast of God’s story.

00:01:07:59.972 --> 00:01:08:03.574
And He wants you to know that story.

00:01:08:03.894 --> 00:01:08:07.876
And as it relates to 'Adamah,

00:01:08:09.217 --> 00:01:08:13.021
look up the story of what is called the red heifer.

00:01:08:15.161 --> 00:01:08:18.444
And it is the 'adamah Parah.

00:01:08:19.385 --> 00:01:08:19.585
Now,

00:01:08:20.204 --> 00:01:08:22.667
Parah does not actually make a girly bull.

00:01:08:23.541 --> 00:01:08:25.402
Par is bull, and yes,

00:01:08:25.903 --> 00:01:08:28.965
Parah could be rendered girly bull and therefore a heifer.

00:01:08:30.185 --> 00:01:08:31.667
That is not the way these words work.

00:01:08:32.268 --> 00:01:08:33.948
The bloody red man of the earth,

00:01:08:34.609 --> 00:01:08:37.431
even though 'adamah has a feminine ending to it,

00:01:08:37.471 --> 00:01:08:39.153
many, many Hebrew words have feminine,

00:01:08:39.172 --> 00:01:08:41.354
all nouns have a feminine or masculine orientation.

00:01:08:46.078 --> 00:01:08:47.640
That does not make them boys or girls, mothers or fathers.

00:01:08:49.654 --> 00:01:08:51.836
It is just a part of the Hebrew grammar.

00:01:08:52.416 --> 00:01:08:56.819
And often when you add the “ah” ending,

00:01:08:57.198 --> 00:01:08:59.341
you expand the connotations of things.

00:01:08:59.421 --> 00:01:09:01.882
A great example would be these 'ets trees.

00:01:09:03.203 --> 00:01:09:06.206
'Ets is the tree as it is presented in Hebrew.

00:01:09:07.557 --> 00:01:09:09.378
The Bare’syth account,

00:01:09:09.399 --> 00:01:09:10.699
we are going to get to that next.

00:01:09:10.760 --> 00:01:09:12.100
It will be on our next program because we are already past the hour.

00:01:09:13.681 --> 00:01:09:16.963
But it is 'etsah when applied to the choter

00:01:09:17.003 --> 00:01:09:21.485
and provided as a spiritual adjunct to the choter’s nature.

00:01:09:23.846 --> 00:01:09:26.588
And the tree 'ets becomes 'etsah,

00:01:09:26.948 --> 00:01:09:28.850
which means that he has the ability to provide counsel and insights

00:01:09:28.890 --> 00:01:09:31.671
on 'etsah, the complete picture that God is presenting.

00:01:09:31.771 --> 00:01:09:34.635
The first person to frame the entire portrait that God has provided

00:01:09:38.037 --> 00:01:09:40.520
and then provide comprehensive counsel on it.

00:01:09:44.662 --> 00:01:09:46.284
It is 'ets to 'etsah.

00:01:09:46.845 --> 00:01:09:47.024
Well,

00:01:09:47.206 --> 00:01:09:50.668
'Adam to 'Adamah does not turn it into a girly shade of red

00:01:09:50.729 --> 00:01:09:53.190
or does not make the man a woman.

00:01:09:55.332 --> 00:01:09:58.815
Well, 'Adam is man, 'Adamah is not woman.

00:01:10:00.256 --> 00:01:10:01.038
Okay,

00:01:10:01.078 --> 00:01:10:05.150
it adds nuances to the man that is being discussed

00:01:10:05.190 --> 00:01:10:07.256
and it makes him a bloody red man of the earth.

00:01:10:09.439 --> 00:01:10:10.100
Okay,

00:01:10:10.121 --> 00:01:10:12.844
so this is God’s way of communicating that par does mean bull.

00:01:10:15.846 --> 00:01:10:20.511
And while Parah, that A-H ending,

00:01:10:20.851 --> 00:01:10:22.353
which is just the hey at the end of the word,

00:01:10:23.314 --> 00:01:10:26.077
what it does is expands our understanding of that bull.

00:01:10:27.238 --> 00:01:10:30.201
And it says that the bull is Parah, which means productive and fruitful.

00:01:10:34.630 --> 00:01:10:36.693
Now for a bull to be productive and fruitful,

00:01:10:36.752 --> 00:01:10:41.220
the bull has many children, offspring.

00:01:10:43.149 --> 00:01:10:45.689
And that bull is part of a harvest that is obviously productive and fruitful.

00:01:10:50.332 --> 00:01:10:50.853
And indeed,

00:01:10:51.193 --> 00:01:10:52.533
that is the role of the 'Adam of Parah.

00:01:10:53.474 --> 00:01:10:55.654
That is the key player in God’s story

00:01:10:55.694 --> 00:01:10:58.377
because ultimately God has three men who are symbolized by three animals.

00:01:11:01.738 --> 00:01:11:04.840
Dowd is the ram and also the Lamb of God.

00:01:11:07.032 --> 00:01:11:10.560
I am the bull and depicted also as the 'adamah Parah

00:01:11:10.720 --> 00:01:11:15.689
and 'Elia who is returning is the goat.

00:01:11:18.788 --> 00:01:11:20.909
And each of them have their specific characteristics.

00:01:11:21.670 --> 00:01:11:24.730
My wife, Leah, presented a song,

00:01:11:25.551 --> 00:01:11:28.893
a video set to music and lyrics that explain the nature of a bull

00:01:11:29.712 --> 00:01:11:34.114
and why that symbol suited the restoring witness of the last days

00:01:11:34.494 --> 00:01:11:36.195
that Yahowah has selected to be this bloody red man of the earth

00:01:11:36.496 --> 00:01:11:41.537
who would be productive and who would fulfill Taruwah

00:01:11:48.541 --> 00:01:11:51.762
purging the remnant of Israel so that they could witness Dowd’s arrival with Yahowah

00:01:11:54.604 --> 00:01:11:58.185
and enter the Gan 'Eden, this sheltered garden for a thousand years

00:01:11:58.225 --> 00:01:11:59.865
during the celebration of Sukkah.

00:01:12:02.487 --> 00:01:12:03.587
There are characteristics

00:01:12:04.957 --> 00:01:12:07.858
that are common among bulls that cause God to say

00:01:12:07.898 --> 00:01:12:09.358
that is a good symbol.

00:01:12:09.417 --> 00:01:12:11.859
People should be able to pursue,

00:01:12:13.779 --> 00:01:12:18.140
be able to understand and process the nature of this man

00:01:12:18.900 --> 00:01:12:21.322
such that you understand his characteristics at this time.

00:01:12:26.224 --> 00:01:12:30.207
A man who is bullish is obviously very positive.

00:01:12:30.247 --> 00:01:12:30.649
We call it a bull market.

00:01:12:30.668 --> 00:01:12:31.710
That would be a positive market.

00:01:12:31.729 --> 00:01:12:34.292
A bullish is aggressive in protecting his own,

00:01:12:34.752 --> 00:01:12:38.716
particularly in protecting women.

00:01:12:41.921 --> 00:01:12:44.923
A bull cannot be a coward.

00:01:12:46.104 --> 00:01:12:47.587
A bull is aggressive.

00:01:12:47.846 --> 00:01:12:48.568
It is forceful.

00:01:12:50.470 --> 00:01:12:52.791
Bulls have interesting characteristics,

00:01:12:53.350 --> 00:01:12:55.351
and there is a whole presentation that Leah has created

00:01:12:55.372 --> 00:01:12:57.113
on my Facebook page, should you be interested in learning about them.

00:01:12:57.153 --> 00:01:12:59.694
So this is the nature of the bull,

00:01:13:03.555 --> 00:01:13:06.015
and that is the 'Adamah Parah that Yahowah has been sacrificed

00:01:13:06.496 --> 00:01:13:11.537
during the celebration of Taruwah.

00:01:13:13.538 --> 00:01:13:15.680
on the twenty-fourth of September of 2033 year 6000 Yah.

00:01:13:18.500 --> 00:01:13:18.800
Yeah.

00:01:13:19.399 --> 00:01:13:22.541
And it fulfills the prophecy of Numbers nineteen

00:01:13:22.621 --> 00:01:13:25.841
pursuant to the adulterous woman of Numbers five

00:01:13:26.061 --> 00:01:13:29.443
so that we can reenter Sukkah and the Garden at that time.

00:01:13:33.939 --> 00:01:13:35.939
So these are the characters in God’s story

00:01:13:36.359 --> 00:01:13:38.039
and what He is achieving with them.

00:01:13:38.079 --> 00:01:13:40.820
And it is a delight to pursue them.

00:01:13:40.860 --> 00:01:13:42.921
And we will return to this spot.

00:01:13:42.981 --> 00:01:13:45.882
I think we will do another program on the same series

00:01:13:45.922 --> 00:01:13:49.764
here later this afternoon.

00:01:13:50.384 --> 00:01:13:51.664
The back held up pretty well.

00:01:13:52.104 --> 00:01:13:54.125
You did not see me wince a single time.

00:01:13:54.666 --> 00:01:13:57.105
So I think we are off and able to do another one this afternoon.

00:01:13:58.487 --> 00:01:13:59.686
So I thank you for listening.

00:01:13:59.747 --> 00:01:14:00.908
I know I got into a lot of

00:01:14:01.627 --> 00:01:14:02.028
questions.

00:01:14:02.793 --> 00:01:14:04.555
really finite detail,

00:01:14:05.115 --> 00:01:14:08.217
but I think it is by exploring the details

00:01:14:08.238 --> 00:01:14:11.140
that we come to know and understand and

00:01:14:11.199 --> 00:01:14:13.721
we become what God is looking for,

00:01:14:14.462 --> 00:01:14:18.045
interesting people that are worthy of His attention

00:01:14:18.085 --> 00:01:14:22.568
over an eternity of time.

00:01:14:22.608 --> 00:01:14:23.548
So thank you for listening.

